<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="544" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1454,1660]" pageId="10" pageNumber="544">
Type data: 
<bibRefCitation author="Friese, H." box="[327,478,1490,1516]" pageId="10" pageNumber="544" pagination="90 - 92" refId="ref6092" refString="Friese, H. (1904) Nachtrag zur Monographie der Bienengattung Centris. Annales Musei Nationalis Hungarici, 2, 90 - 92." type="journal article" year="1904">Friese (1904)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that two of the six type specimens were housed at 
<collectionCode box="[1194,1283,1490,1516]" country="Hungary" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="10" pageNumber="544">HNHM</collectionCode>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." pageId="10" pageNumber="544" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref6580" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Eds.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis box="[1379,1429,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="544">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated that the type series was housed at 
<collectionCode box="[738,826,1526,1552]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="10" pageNumber="544">AMNH</collectionCode>
, but it was not found there. The two males housed at 
<collectionCode box="[151,237,1562,1588]" country="Hungary" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="10" pageNumber="544">HNHM</collectionCode>
mentioned by Friese were effectively found in that collection and both have the same provenance label: Costa-Rica Schild. [printed]. These specimens are here designated 
<typeStatus box="[900,1003,1598,1624]" pageId="10" pageNumber="544">lectotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus box="[1057,1212,1598,1624]" pageId="10" pageNumber="544">paralectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
